Description: Left Handed, Lefty 1988 S-600 Epiphone by Gibson Super Strat, excellent condition. It has new strings and been professionally set-up. I’ve played it maybe 6 times since I purchased it a few years ago. Too many guitars! Here we have one of few collectable Asian-produced guitars - and its in excellent condition! A one-owner, Epiphone by Gibson S-600 "Super Strat." Produced almost 30 years ago in the Samick facility, Korea, 1988. Features the famous Steinberger locking tremolo system, shark tooth inlays and killer sounding HSS pickups. Finish is in excellent condition with one chip on the front of the body shown in the pictures. Maple neck with rosewood fingerboard and pearloid "shark tooth" inlays. Frets are in great shape with hardly any wear. Pointed headstock with mother of pearl "Epiphone By Gibson" inlay. Black mini tuners are in perfect working condition. One tuner has been replaced, but I can also send original if you'd like to try and fix. 1 5/8" nut width; 25 1/2" scale length. Neck is straight & truss rod works fine. Contoured, solid body finished in midnight metallic black. Tremolo bridge with adjustable saddles. Includes original tremolo arm. Schaller strap locks installed.  Epiphone HSS pickups. Master volume and dual tone controls with black knurled knobs and 5-way selector switch.
